tab to complete

ctrl-r to search through command history. press ctrl-r repeatedlly to cycle through more matches,press Enter to execute the found command,or hit the right arrow to put the result in the current line to allow editing.

ctrl-w to delete the last word
ctrl-u to delete the content from current cursor back to the start of the line

alt-b alt-f to move back or forword by word

find . -name '*.py' | xargs grep 'datetime.now()'
